    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Components of a RAG\n### Retrieval Augmented Generation:\n- before the LLM receives the user query, reference information is retrieved from in information base\n- that information is provided to the LLM together with the user query to \"anchor\" the answer\n- system prompt and quality of the retrieval in key\n\n### Demo shows the two steps: \n#### Create the information base\n- Document is loaded into a `vector database` using the **Load Data** flow,\n#### Retrieve relevant info from the base\n- use query and chat context to retrieve relevant info using the **Retriever** flow.\n\n### Quick start\n1. Click on the `Execute Workflow` button to run the  **Load Data** flow.\n2. Click on `Open Chat` button to run the  **Retriever** flow. Then ask a question about content from your document(s)\n\n### More info:\n- Key node for this workflow is the `Simple Vector Store` node, used in several configurations:\n    - \"add document to vector store\"\n    - \"retrieve document (as tool to agent)\"\n- Check `Simple Vector Store` [node documentation](https://docs.n8n.io/integrations/builtin/cluster-nodes/root-nodes/n8n-nodes-langchain.vectorstoreinmemory)\n- Check `Default Data Loader` [node documentation](https://docs.n8n.io/integrations/builtin/cluster-nodes/sub-nodes/n8n-nodes-langchain.documentdefaultdataloader/)\n- Check [docs on RAG in n8n](https://docs.n8n.io/advanced-ai/rag-in-n8n/).\n",
        "height": 780,
        "width": 440,
        "color": 5
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        -656,
        -192
      ],
